<HEAD>Twenty Children Slightly Injured in Mishap</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A school bus with an allegedly drunken driver at the wheel flipped over a curb onto its side, slightly injuring 20 schoolchildren, police said. The bus carrying the 20 children home from school went out of control on the city's <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Side </LOCATION> on Friday, police said. Charges of driving under the influence and operating a school bus while intoxicated, a felony, were filed against the driver, <PERSON> Ocie </PERSON> <PERSON> Hendricks </PERSON>, 53, after he refused a breathalizer test, said <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> Police Sgt. <PERSON> Gerald </PERSON> <PERSON> Satala </PERSON>. <PERSON> Hendricks </PERSON>, being held at the district station until a bond hearing today, could be jailed for up to three years if convicted of the felony charge, <PERSON> Satala </PERSON> said. The children were treated for minor injuries at four area hospitals, said Fire Department spokesman <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Sheppard </PERSON>. Their age range was not immediately available, though the children at one of the hospital were ages 9 to 14. Witnesses at the scene said the bus was traveling 40 mph in a 15 mph zone, but that could not be immediately confirmed by police.
