very evening for `` long political gossips'' and `` partly to keep me awake so that I did n't go to sleep too early and therefore have a bad night. I found his depth of knowledge of many subjects particularly history and politics, fascinating.'' <ORGANIZATION> Conservative </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> chairman <PERSON> Kenneth </PERSON> <PERSON> Clarke </PERSON> said <PERSON> Trafford </PERSON>'s death was a `` loss to the government and a loss to the public life of this country.'' Trafford is survived by his wife, <PERSON> Helen </PERSON>, and a son and a daughter.
